  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Saving children born without an immune system</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">70% of all the children with a Primary Immunodeficiency need an antibodies replacement treatment in order to survive. Poor families do not have medical social security to cover the treatment. This antibodies replacement treatment is available in Mexico. However, it is only guaranteed  for children 5 years old or younger by the Mexican Public Health Ministry. We is seeking to work alongside with the Mexican Public Health authorities and families to modify Public Health Policies and Laws</narrative>
  </description>
